ind.kdtree

Class KDNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • ind.kdtree.KDNode
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<KDNode>

    public class KDNode
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<KDNode>
    Implements a node of a k-d-tree. Every node has a point (image), a dimension (k), a depth, a descriptor type and references to the parent and the child nodes. This class offers overridden compareTo and equals functions.
    Author:
    Matej Stanic

    • Method Detail

      • compareTo

        public static int compareTo(int depth,
            int k,
            ImageContainer image1,
            ImageContainer image2,
            DescriptorType type)
        Compares the values of the actual splitting coordinate of two node descriptors.
        Parameters:
        depth - The depth of the actual node.
        k - The dimensionality of the actual node descriptor.
        image1 - The actual node image.
        image2 - The node image which is compared.
        type - The descriptor type used.
        Returns:
        -1 if descriptor1[dim] is smaller than descriptor2[dim] 0 if they are the same and 1 if descriptor1[dim] is bigger than descriptor2[dim].
